  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). A governing requirement mandates experimental-validation as the required verification method for the hemolysis QoI; however, the supporting validation activity was conducted as a numerical simulation whose results are argued to be 'as good as' bench-top experimental data, without a formal equivalence substitution in the structured record.",
