      "name": "Relative Hemolysis Index Comparison — Numerical Simulation vs. Predicate Reference",
      "description": "Predicted RH values across all 5 flow-speed operating points were compared against predicate device hemolysis reference values. The comparison shows RH < 1 at all operating points (max RH = 0.87). The assessment team notes that the high-fidelity CFD results, incorporating validated turbulence and blood damage models, are considered functionally equivalent to an experimental bench measurement for the purpose of this submission. No physical hemolysis experiment was conducted; the activity was a numerical simulation using the same mesh and solver settings as the primary predictive model.",
